PassiveHOst Detection PHD
-------------------------

Passive Host Detection is a application that is meant to capture packets from a designated network interface, in order to identify network devices on the network.

It is a user space application at this point in time with the view to added especially a linux driver to bind to the network interface in the future.


Why PHD?
--------

The aim of PHD is to provide a opensource alternative to comercially available alternaties like centennial's LANProbe.


How Does PHD do this?
---------------------

Is this all that the project hopes to do?
-----------------------------------------

No, we intend once PHD is complete, to create a system that can rival software products like Centennial Discovery 
